Each local search and rescue coordinator shall assist local rescue squads in developing a comprehensive written search and rescue plan which shall address as a minimum:
Direction and control responsibilities or incident command system procedures;
Notification and reporting procedures and requirements;
Call-out procedures;
Resource identification;
Coordination of resources;
Mutual aid agreements;
Training requirements for search and rescue responders and managers;
Coordination of all on-scene operations with other local, state, and federal agencies; and
The provision of copies of topographical maps for search team members.
